<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="1402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1402">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.4016/74</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                            <gloss type="from">
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-16T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>865. Your 841, July 10. Department approves your procedure in pleading
                            with Turkish Minister of Interior and Minister of War to stop Armenian
                            persecution and in attempting to enlist sympathies of German and
                            Austrian Ambassadors in this cause. The Department can offer no
                            additional suggestions relative to this most difficult situation other
                            than that you continue to act as in the past. Have any native-born
                            American citizens or any naturalized American citizens entitled to
                            protection under American statutes received injuries during this
                            trouble?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>